external_knowledge:
- 'storminess' refers to the average combined volatility (the sum of the 30-day rolling volatility and 30-day rolling annualized volatility) of a stock; 
- 'navigating through multiple market conditions' implies that a stock has more than one entry in the database for a specific date; 
- 'turbulent stocks' are those with the highest 30-day rolling volatility within their industry.

sql:
SELECT user_id
FROM portfolio
WHERE weightage = (SELECT MAX(weightage) FROM portfolio);

SELECT stock_id, current_day_underlying_daily_volatility, rolling_annualized_volatility_30d
FROM annualized_volatility
WHERE rolling_annualized_volatility_90d > 0.03;
